redis: Add username

Redis introduced ACL feature in 4.0.0, and this feature is supported by redis-py since 3.4.0[1]. When ACL is enabled, authentication requires username in addition to password.

This adds the username argument to Redis backend and Redis Sentinel backend, so that username can be passed in arguments along with password, instead of using client_kwargs and sentinel_kwargs.

[1] https://github.com/redis/redis-py/commit/8df8cd54d135380ad8b3b8807a67a3e6915b0b49

add method to get the CachedValue / cached time directly

Added new method :meth:`.CacheRegion.get_value_metadata` which can be used
to get a value from the cache along with its metadata, including timestamp
of when the value was cached.  The :class:`.CachedValue` object is returned
which features new accessors to retrieve cached time and current age. Pull
request courtesy Grégoire Deveaux.
